invoke a command at a given date/time or when a criteria is met
    -at=12:00
       waits until 12:00 before executing the provided cmd
         (time format)
       if that time has already passed, it will wait until the following day
    -at=00:00:00
       waits until 00:00:00 before executing the provided cmd
         (seconds format)
       if that time has already passed, it will wait until the following day
    -at=2022/05/06 00:00:00 <date format>
       waits until 00:00:00 of the given date before executing the provided cmd
         (seconds format)
       if that time has already passed, an error will be raised and the cmd will return immediately
    -file=<file to execute>
        _TIME_FILE
    -execute=<cmd with arguments to execute>
        _TIME_EXECUTE
    -cleanup
        cleanup the file on successful execution
examples
  when-at -at=12:00 -file="/tmp/test.sh"
  when-at -at=12:00 -execute="sh /tmp/test.sh"
  when-at -at=12:00 -execute="sh /tmp/test.sh 1 2 3 a b c"
  when-at -at=12:00 -execute="printf 'hi\n'"
  when-at -at=00:00:00 -execute="printf hi\n"
  when-at -at="2025/11/21 00:00:00" -execute="printf hi\n"
    if the time has already passed, an error will be generated
  when-at -at="2025/11/22 00:00:00" -execute="printf hi\n"
    will wait until the specified time
